	"name":"Why do I also need a shield _without_ Turtling?",
	"value": "During Phase 4, there is a strategy called clone skip. This results in a 33.6s time save across a kill if done correctly, and substantially decreases the duration of the phase. However, one side effect is that it means that if you handle the first weekly special in Phase 4 with barricade using turtling, it will not be off cooldown for the second instance of the weekly special in that phase. In some weeks, this can lead to pk'ing your teammate. By bringing a non-turtling shield specifically for phase 4, this is no longer an issue and leads to a much smoother kill. This can be done either using an Elder Rune +5 shield, or a T80 Defender. If you own the Malletops perk (T2) from Ranch Out Of time (117 Farming), then a t80 defender barricade lasts the duration of intercept."
